# Default profile: LGPL, audio-only ffmpeg.wasm core.
#
# ffmpeg is configured with --disable-everything and NO --enable-gpl / --enable-nonfree, then only
# audio components are re-enabled — all are ffmpeg's NATIVE codecs or permissive (BSD) external
# libs, so the binary stays LGPL (AGPL-compatible), with no GPL/patent VIDEO encoder (x264/x265).
#
# Codec / PATENT posture (copyleft is clean; patents are a separate, jurisdiction-specific matter):
#   - Truly royalty-free: Opus, Vorbis, FLAC, PCM, ALAC, WavPack, TTA.
#   - Core patents expired / commonly treated as license-free: AAC-LC, AC-3, DTS Coherent Acoustics
#     ("DTS core", decoder `dca`).
#   - E-AC-3 (Dolby Digital Plus) is NEWER; some patents may still be active in your jurisdiction —
#     included at the maintainer's discretion. HE-AAC/xHE-AAC, TrueHD/MLP and DTS-HD/MA are NOT
#     included (see profiles/full.env.example).
# These are all DECODERS (inputs to transcode). The ENCODED OUTPUT is only Opus or AAC-LC.
#
# Data flow: the WASM core hands ffmpeg a self-contained Matroska chunk of raw audio frames; ffmpeg
# decodes it and re-encodes to fragmented MP4 for MSE. Exactly one demuxer (matroska) and one muxer
# (mp4, +mov base) are needed — the mp4 muxer is essential (it is not patent-encumbered).
FFMPEG_CONF="--disable-everything \
--enable-libopus --enable-libvorbis --enable-zlib \
--enable-decoder=libvorbis,vorbis,libopus,opus,flac,alac,wavpack,tta,aac,ac3,eac3,dca,pcm_s16le,pcm_s16be,pcm_s24le,pcm_s24be,pcm_s32le,pcm_f32le,pcm_u8 \
--enable-encoder=libopus,aac,flac \
--enable-demuxer=matroska \
--enable-muxer=mp4,mov \
--enable-parser=opus,vorbis,flac,aac,ac3,dca \
--enable-filter=aresample,aformat,anull \
--enable-protocol=file"

FFMPEG_LINK_LIBS="-lopus -lvorbis -lvorbisenc -lvorbisfile -logg -lz"
